Lagos- The Department of Petroleum Resources (DPR),Tuesday advised consumers to report any infraction such as under dispensing of products to its offices nationwide. The agency conveyed this advice through its Head, Public Affairs, Paul Osu, who also assured Nigerians of petroleum products availability during the yuletide period. He revealed that there is product sufficiency nationwide and advised marketers against hoarding and creating artificial scarcity. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He promised that his agency would intensify its monitoring and surveillance of Petroleum products outlets to ensure compliance with quality, quantity and safety of operations in line with its regulatory mandate. He restated DPR’s commitment to safety and advised consumers to observe all necessary safety protocols in the handling of Petroleum products especially at this season of harmattan. NSE Launches X-PO Electronic Platform For Public Offerings Subscription Makinde Harps On Zero Tolerance For Corruption, Inaugurates State’s Agency According to him, the agency will continue to initiate appropriate initiatives to enable business and create opportunities for investors and stakeholders in the oil and gas industry in Nigeria. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION